  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " He cites this testimony to prove that none of the forementioned evils, no, not death itself, can separate believers from the love of Christ: it is taken out of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Psalm 44:22",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Psalm 44:22",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The argument seems to be this: The saints of old have endured all manner of sufferings, and yet were not separated from the love of God; therefore such sufferings cannot separate them now. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "For thy sake; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " not for our sins’ sake, but for Christ’s, or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "for righteousness’ sake, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " Matthew 5:10 10:18,39 1 Peter 3:14",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 5:10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " 10:18,39 ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Peter 3:14",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "We are killed:",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " how could they say this? Killing takes away all complaining, and makes the parties so dealt with incapable of saying how it is with them. This expression notes the danger and desperateness of their condition. It is usual in Scripture to set forth an eminent danger under the notion of death: see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "1 Corinthians 15:31 2 Corinthians 1:10 4:11",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Corinthians 15:31",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Corinthians 1:10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " 4:11",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "All the day long; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " i.e. continually, without ceasing: see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Psalm 38:6,12 71:24 73:14 Proverbs 23:17 Romans 10:21",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Psalm 38:6",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ",12 71:24 73:14 ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 23:17",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
